         It's been pointed out in this thread already, but it's to save you and your pet when a train hits.</P><P>What if you are feigned near an AoE casting Dragon and the only critter around is your pet. 5 Seconds later you aren't feigned anymore because that Dragon just AoE'd on your pet and hit you too. This problem gets exponentially worse as you add more Dragons to this. (Meaning you won't get feign off a second time.)</P><P>What if you are feigned near a corpse camping mob and you have 10 hit points. This would give time for you to get a heal, regen then have the pet tank the mob while you get back up and start fighting. (Even if it's 2 minutes worth of regen that's 20 ticks of health.)</P><P>If you are pulling in a tight area and get adds and your pet jumps into the fray to protect you from the adds you can feign, have your pet feign and wait till it's clear to resume pulling.</P><P>Jump into PoF/PoG (Or similar aggro heavy zone), Summon a pet, get aggro.. you two Feign till stuff walks back.. get up and be ready to rock.</P><P>Mob gates, your pet gets summoned... feign him and summon him back to your side.</P><P>There are a lot more places where this skill will be useful (Not to mention saving the mage the trouble of summoning a suit of armor and muzzle again.)</P><P>A little imagination would go a long way with this ability. I'll get it.</P><P><BR><img src="http://www.jackntracie.com/images/gojirax.jpg" border=0><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
